v:cp.v:prompt: Select the set of custom properties to display then close and re-open the custom properties window.

Enter the fully qualified object reference of the object that this shape will be bound to. If this shape is aliased enter a partial reference. The binding reference for this shape will be the concatenation of the network alias value (if set), the system alias value (if set) and this property.

Enter the name of the local variable that contains the network portion of the object reference that this shape is to bind to. Enter <none> if you do not wish to use a network alias. If set, the bound reference is the concatenation of the value of network alias variable, the value of the system alias variable (if set) and the object reference property.

Enter the name of the local variable that contains the system portion of the object reference that this shape is to bind to. Enter <none> if you do not wish to use a system alias. If set, the bound reference is the concatenation of the value of network alias variable (if set), the value of the system alias variable and the object reference property.
Select whether any bindings will occur at all on this shape. This setting overrides all others. Setting this property to false will make the shape completely static.
Select whether any portion of the shape will attempt to bind to an Alarm extension. This setting will override other Alarm properties.

Enter the Object name of the Alarm extension you wish this shape to bind to for alarm indication purposes. Hover the mouse cursor over desired alarmed attribute in the Alarm view to see the ref of the Alarm object.
Use Extreme Caution before editing. This property contains the JavaScript formula to concatenate the network, system and objref fields at runtime, subject to the alias enables.

Select whether the tooltip displays the bound object's Name (.2390) .
Select whether the tooltip displays the (calculated) object reference the shape is attempting to bind to.
Select whether the tooltip displays the bound object's Description (.28).
Select whether the tooltip displays the Alarm Message Text (.Alarm1.537) of the Alarm Extension when the object is in alarm.
Enter the name of the font the tooltip will use. Remember that the client must already have this font. There is no auto-download mechanism.
